[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":724},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F12\u002F28\u002Fnodejs-nodemailer-gmail-oauth2\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F12\u002F28\u002Fnodejs-nodemailer-gmail-oauth2\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F12\u002F28\u002Fnodejs-nodemailer-gmail-oauth2\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F12\u002F28\u002Fnodejs-nodemailer-gmail-oauth2\u002F":699,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F12\u002F28\u002Fnodejs-nodemailer-gmail-oauth2\u002F":708},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20191228\u002F1009061739\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":678,"date":679,"description":680,"extension":681,"lang":682,"meta":683,"navigation":684,"path":685,"readingMinutes":686,"seo":687,"standalone":688,"stem":689,"tags":690,"tldr":695,"updated":696,"url":697,"__hash__":698},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fnodejs-nodemailer-gmail-oauth2.md","Sending Gmail with nodemailer After Google Killed Password Auth (OAuth 2.0)","1002272756",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":670},"minimark",[11,31,36,39,43,46,158,161,169,172,176,186,193,196,202,209,214,221,226,236,241,246,259,264,274,279,294,300,307,312,315,321,331,336,343,348,365,370,373,379,383,390,395,407,413,416,422,425,431,434,440,443,448,451,457,460,464,477,604,612,615,623,627,666],[12,13,14],"blockquote",{},[15,16,17,21,22,27,28],"p",{},[18,19,20],"strong",{},"Note","\nThis post is pretty old now, so I rewrote a fresh tutorial — you can ",[23,24,26],"a",{"href":25},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20230722\u002F1626712457\u002F","jump straight to it here"," (article in Mandarin).\nI'm keeping this one around as a learning record ",[29,30],"d",{},[32,33,35],"h2",{"id":34},"intro","Intro",[15,37,38],{},"This time I want to add an extra note about nodemailer. Google no longer accepts plain username-and-password auth for sending Gmail, so I'm writing down how to set things up using Express + OAuth 2.0 + nodemailer + Gmail instead.",[32,40,42],{"id":41},"why-this-changed","Why this changed",[15,44,45],{},"In the original chapter, the nodemailer setup looked like this:",[47,48,53],"pre",{"className":49,"code":50,"language":51,"meta":52,"style":52},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","var transporter = nodemailer.createTransport({\n  service: 'Gmail'\n  host: \"smtp.ethereal.email\",\n  port: 587,\n  auth: { \u002F\u002F The account and password used to send mail — you can switch to dotenv later to keep your credentials safe\n    user: 'XXX@gmail.com',\n    pass: 'Paswword'\n  }\n});\n","js","",[54,55,56,82,92,104,116,126,137,146,152],"code",{"__ignoreMap":52},[57,58,61,65,69,72,75,79],"span",{"class":59,"line":60},"line",1,[57,62,64],{"class":63},"sWyjQ","var",[57,66,68],{"class":67},"sMAXC"," transporter ",[57,70,71],{"class":63},"=",[57,73,74],{"class":67}," nodemailer.",[57,76,78],{"class":77},"sj_SG","createTransport",[57,80,81],{"class":67},"({\n",[57,83,85,88],{"class":59,"line":84},2,[57,86,87],{"class":67},"  service: ",[57,89,91],{"class":90},"sTRMh","'Gmail'\n",[57,93,95,98,101],{"class":59,"line":94},3,[57,96,97],{"class":67},"  host: ",[57,99,100],{"class":90},"\"smtp.ethereal.email\"",[57,102,103],{"class":67},",\n",[57,105,107,110,114],{"class":59,"line":106},4,[57,108,109],{"class":67},"  port: ",[57,111,113],{"class":112},"sCcAr","587",[57,115,103],{"class":67},[57,117,119,122],{"class":59,"line":118},5,[57,120,121],{"class":67},"  auth: { ",[57,123,125],{"class":124},"sQrFR","\u002F\u002F The account and password used to send mail — you can switch to dotenv later to keep your credentials safe\n",[57,127,129,132,135],{"class":59,"line":128},6,[57,130,131],{"class":67},"    user: ",[57,133,134],{"class":90},"'XXX@gmail.com'",[57,136,103],{"class":67},[57,138,140,143],{"class":59,"line":139},7,[57,141,142],{"class":67},"    pass: ",[57,144,145],{"class":90},"'Paswword'\n",[57,147,149],{"class":59,"line":148},8,[57,150,151],{"class":67},"  }\n",[57,153,155],{"class":59,"line":154},9,[57,156,157],{"class":67},"});\n",[15,159,160],{},"But these days Google has changed how it authenticates, so it no longer accepts logging in with a username and password. You'll end up with this error:",[47,162,167],{"className":163,"code":165,"language":166,"meta":52},[164],"language-text","535-5.7.8 Username and Password not accepted. Learn more at\\n535 5.7.8  https:\u002F\u002Fsupport.google.com\u002Fmail\u002F?p=BadCredentials d5sm35056162pfd.107 - gsmtp\n","text",[54,168,165],{"__ignoreMap":52},[15,170,171],{},"nodemailer's own docs also recommend switching to OAuth2, so this post fills in the gap on how to send Gmail through OAuth.",[32,173,175],{"id":174},"step-1-create-the-oauth-client","Step 1 — Create the OAuth client",[15,177,178,179,185],{},"First, head over to ",[23,180,184],{"href":181,"rel":182},"https:\u002F\u002Fconsole.cloud.google.com\u002F",[183],"nofollow","Google Cloud Platform"," and create a new project.",[15,187,188],{},[189,190],"img",{"alt":191,"src":192},"Create a new project in the top left","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F201912271101-1.png",[15,194,195],{},"Name the project whatever you want — I called mine Gmail Test.",[15,197,198],{},[189,199],{"alt":200,"src":201},"Gmail Test","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F201912271101-2.png",[15,203,204,205,208],{},"Next, open the side menu and you'll see ",[18,206,207],{},"APIs & Services",".",[15,210,211],{},[189,212],{"alt":207,"src":213},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F201912271101-3.png",[15,215,216,217,220],{},"On the APIs & Services page, click ",[18,218,219],{},"Enable APIs and Services"," at the top.",[15,222,223],{},[189,224],{"alt":219,"src":225},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F201912271101-4.png",[15,227,228,229,232,233,208],{},"Then search for ",[18,230,231],{},"Gmail API",", click into it, and hit ",[18,234,235],{},"Enable",[15,237,238],{},[189,239],{"alt":231,"src":240},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F201912271101-5.png",[15,242,243],{},[189,244],{"alt":235,"src":245},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F201912271101-6.png",[15,247,248,249,252,253,252,256,208],{},"Once the Gmail API is enabled, go to ",[18,250,251],{},"Credentials"," → ",[18,254,255],{},"Create Credentials",[18,257,258],{},"OAuth client ID",[15,260,261],{},[189,262],{"alt":258,"src":263},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F201912271101-7.png",[15,265,266,267,270,271,208],{},"At this point Google will probably tell you \"To create an OAuth client ID, you must first configure your product name on the consent screen.\" So click in and set it up. One thing to watch — for ",[18,268,269],{},"User Type",", pick ",[18,272,273],{},"External",[15,275,276],{},[189,277],{"alt":269,"src":278},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F201912271101-8.png",[15,280,281,282,285,286,289,290,293],{},"Then fill in the ",[18,283,284],{},"app name",", ",[18,287,288],{},"user support email",", and ",[18,291,292],{},"developer contact information"," and you can submit (it's just for testing anyway). Don't sweat the rest — just keep hitting save and continue.",[15,295,296],{},[189,297],{"alt":298,"src":299},"OAuth consent screen","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F%E7%B7%A8%E8%BC%AF%E6%87%89%E7%94%A8%E7%A8%8B%E5%BC%8F%E8%A8%BB%E5%86%8A%E7%94%B3%E8%AB%8B_%E2%80%93_API_%E5%92%8C%E6%9C%8D%E5%8B%99_%E2%80%93_My_Project_66676_%E2%80%93_Google_Cloud_Platform.png",[15,301,302,303,306],{},"Here's an important bit: newer Google OAuth requires you to add test users. So at the ",[18,304,305],{},"Test users"," step (step 3), you have to add the account you'll actually test with (a Google account). Make sure this is the exact account you're going to use with Node.js — not some random account you threw in.",[15,308,309],{},[189,310],{"alt":305,"src":311},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F202104060923.png",[15,313,314],{},"If you skip adding a test user, you'll hit this screen later in the flow.",[15,316,317],{},[189,318],{"alt":319,"src":320},"Error 403: access_denied","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F202104060927.png",[15,322,323,324,252,326,252,328,330],{},"Now go back to ",[18,325,251],{},[18,327,255],{},[18,329,258],{}," again.",[15,332,333],{},[189,334],{"alt":258,"src":335},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F202104060914.png",[15,337,338,339,342],{},"When you choose here, make sure you pick ",[18,340,341],{},"Web application"," — not Desktop app, Chrome app, or anything else. If you choose something other than Web application, you won't be able to continue.",[15,344,345],{},[189,346],{"alt":341,"src":347},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F202104060915.png",[15,349,350,351,354,355,359,360,364],{},"Next, under ",[18,352,353],{},"Authorized redirect URIs",", click \"Add URI\" and enter \"",[23,356,357],{"href":357,"rel":358},"https:\u002F\u002Fdevelopers.google.com\u002Foauthplayground",[183],"\". Don't enter \"",[23,361,362],{"href":362,"rel":363},"https:\u002F\u002Fdevelopers.google.com\u002Foauthplayground\u002F",[183],"\" with the trailing slash — that will absolutely break authorization.",[15,366,367],{},[189,368],{"alt":353,"src":369},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F202104060918.png",[15,371,372],{},"Finally you'll get your Client ID and Client Secret. Keep them somewhere safe — you'll need them shortly.",[15,374,375],{},[189,376],{"alt":377,"src":378},"Client ID and Client Secret","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F201912271101-11.png",[32,380,382],{"id":381},"step-2-get-the-refresh-token-and-access-token","Step 2 — Get the refresh token and access token",[15,384,385,386,389],{},"Now open this URL: ",[23,387,357],{"href":357,"rel":388},[183],". Click the gear icon in the top right, check \"Use your own OAuth credentials\", and enter the Client ID and Client Secret you just got.",[15,391,392],{},[189,393],{"alt":377,"src":394},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002FUse%20your%20own%20OAuth%20credentials.png",[15,396,397,398,402,403,406],{},"Then in the left-hand input box, enter \"",[23,399,400],{"href":400,"rel":401},"https:\u002F\u002Fmail.google.com\u002F",[183],"\" — or find \"Gmail API V1\", pick ",[23,404,400],{"href":400,"rel":405},[183],", and click Authorize APIs.",[15,408,409],{},[189,410],{"alt":411,"src":412},"Authorize APIs","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F201912271101-13.png",[15,414,415],{},"When you click Authorize APIs, you'll be taken to that familiar Google sign-in screen. If you have multiple accounts, pick the right one.",[15,417,418],{},[189,419],{"alt":420,"src":421},"Pick the right account","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F201912271101-14.png",[15,423,424],{},"This screen looks a little scary, but don't worry — it's our own app, so it's fine.",[15,426,427],{},[189,428],{"alt":429,"src":430},"This app isn't verified by Google","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-04-06%2009.28.38.png",[15,432,433],{},"Google takes user permissions seriously, so it'll ask you one more time.",[15,435,436],{},[189,437],{"alt":438,"src":439},"User permissions","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F201912271101-16.png",[15,441,442],{},"Yeah... see? Google really does care about your account security.",[15,444,445],{},[189,446],{"alt":438,"src":447},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F201912271101-17.png",[15,449,450],{},"Now you'll find yourself back at the original screen. Click \"Exchange authorization code for tokens\".",[15,452,453],{},[189,454],{"alt":455,"src":456},"Exchange authorization code for tokens","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002FExchange%20authorization%20code%20for%20tokens.png",[15,458,459],{},"At this point you'll get both an Access token and a Refresh token. Write both of them down.",[32,461,463],{"id":462},"step-3-update-nodemailer","Step 3 — Update nodemailer",[15,465,466,467,285,470,289,473,476],{},"Finally, head back to our earlier project. Like I mentioned, the original code logged in with a plain username and password to use nodemailer, so we need to adjust it a bit. Basically, you pass in ",[54,468,469],{},"clientId",[54,471,472],{},"clientSecret",[54,474,475],{},"refreshToken"," via environment variables and change the code to this:",[47,478,480],{"className":49,"code":479,"language":51,"meta":52,"style":52},"const transporter = nodemailer.createTransport({\n  host: 'smtp.gmail.com',\n  port: 465,\n  secure: true,\n  auth: {\n    type: \"OAuth2\",\n    user: process.env.ACCOUNT,\n    clientId: process.env.CLINENTID,\n    clientSecret: process.env.CLINENTSECRET,\n    refreshToken: process.env.REFRESHTOKEN,\n    accessToken: process.env.ACCESSTOKEN,\n  }\n});\n",[54,481,482,499,508,517,527,532,542,552,562,572,583,594,599],{"__ignoreMap":52},[57,483,484,487,490,493,495,497],{"class":59,"line":60},[57,485,486],{"class":63},"const",[57,488,489],{"class":112}," transporter",[57,491,492],{"class":63}," =",[57,494,74],{"class":67},[57,496,78],{"class":77},[57,498,81],{"class":67},[57,500,501,503,506],{"class":59,"line":84},[57,502,97],{"class":67},[57,504,505],{"class":90},"'smtp.gmail.com'",[57,507,103],{"class":67},[57,509,510,512,515],{"class":59,"line":94},[57,511,109],{"class":67},[57,513,514],{"class":112},"465",[57,516,103],{"class":67},[57,518,519,522,525],{"class":59,"line":106},[57,520,521],{"class":67},"  secure: ",[57,523,524],{"class":112},"true",[57,526,103],{"class":67},[57,528,529],{"class":59,"line":118},[57,530,531],{"class":67},"  auth: {\n",[57,533,534,537,540],{"class":59,"line":128},[57,535,536],{"class":67},"    type: ",[57,538,539],{"class":90},"\"OAuth2\"",[57,541,103],{"class":67},[57,543,544,547,550],{"class":59,"line":139},[57,545,546],{"class":67},"    user: process.env.",[57,548,549],{"class":112},"ACCOUNT",[57,551,103],{"class":67},[57,553,554,557,560],{"class":59,"line":148},[57,555,556],{"class":67},"    clientId: process.env.",[57,558,559],{"class":112},"CLINENTID",[57,561,103],{"class":67},[57,563,564,567,570],{"class":59,"line":154},[57,565,566],{"class":67},"    clientSecret: process.env.",[57,568,569],{"class":112},"CLINENTSECRET",[57,571,103],{"class":67},[57,573,575,578,581],{"class":59,"line":574},10,[57,576,577],{"class":67},"    refreshToken: process.env.",[57,579,580],{"class":112},"REFRESHTOKEN",[57,582,103],{"class":67},[57,584,586,589,592],{"class":59,"line":585},11,[57,587,588],{"class":67},"    accessToken: process.env.",[57,590,591],{"class":112},"ACCESSTOKEN",[57,593,103],{"class":67},[57,595,597],{"class":59,"line":596},12,[57,598,151],{"class":67},[57,600,602],{"class":59,"line":601},13,[57,603,157],{"class":67},[15,605,606,607,611],{},"If you're unsure about the env part, you can look back at ",[23,608,610],{"href":609},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20190702\u002F3749489780\u002F","this post"," (article in Mandarin).",[15,613,614],{},"Congrats — you've got nodemailer sending mail through OAuth.",[15,616,617,618,208],{},"And as usual, here's the ",[23,619,622],{"href":620,"rel":621},"https:\u002F\u002Fpeaceful-hot-springs-27518.herokuapp.com\u002Fusers\u002Fmailsend",[183],"Heroku test site",[32,624,626],{"id":625},"references","References",[628,629,630,638,645,652,659],"ul",{},[631,632,633],"li",{},[23,634,637],{"href":635,"rel":636},"https:\u002F\u002Ftanaikech.github.io\u002F2018\u002F01\u002F08\u002Fsend-mails-from-gmail-using-nodemailer\u002F",[183],"Send mails from Gmail using Nodemailer",[631,639,640],{},[23,641,644],{"href":642,"rel":643},"https:\u002F\u002Fmedium.com\u002F@nickroach_50526\u002Fsending-emails-with-node-js-using-smtp-gmail-and-oauth2-316fe9c790a1",[183],"Sending Emails with Node.js Using SMTP, Gmail, and OAuth2",[631,646,647],{},[23,648,651],{"href":649,"rel":650},"https:\u002F\u002Fmedium.com\u002F@RistaSB\u002Fuse-expressjs-to-send-mails-with-gmail-oauth-2-0-and-nodemailer-d585bba71343",[183],"Use Expressjs to send mails with gmail OAuth 2.0 and nodemailer",[631,653,654],{},[23,655,658],{"href":656,"rel":657},"https:\u002F\u002Fnodemailer.com\u002Fsmtp\u002Foauth2\u002F#oauth-2lo",[183],"OAUTH2",[631,660,661],{},[23,662,665],{"href":663,"rel":664},"https:\u002F\u002Fstackoverflow.com\u002Fquestions\u002F24098461\u002Fnodemailer-gmail-what-exactly-is-a-refresh-token-and-how-do-i-get-one",[183],"Nodemailer\u002FGmail - What exactly is a refresh token and how do I get one?",[667,668,669],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sWyjQ, html code.shiki .sWyjQ{--shiki-default:#FF9492}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sj_SG, html code.shiki .sj_SG{--shiki-default:#DBB7FF}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}html pre.shiki code .sQrFR, html code.shiki .sQrFR{--shiki-default:#BDC4CC}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}",{"title":52,"searchDepth":84,"depth":84,"links":671},[672,673,674,675,676,677],{"id":34,"depth":84,"text":35},{"id":41,"depth":84,"text":42},{"id":174,"depth":84,"text":175},{"id":381,"depth":84,"text":382},{"id":462,"depth":84,"text":463},{"id":625,"depth":84,"text":626},"Nodejs","2019-12-28 00:26:06","This time I want to add an extra note about nodemailer. Google no longer lets you send Gmail messages with just a username and password, so I'm writing down how to set up Express + OAuth 2.0 + nodemailer + Gmail instead. It's a quick walkthrough — building the OAuth client, grabbing the refresh and access tokens, and wiring them into nodemailer.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002Fnodejs-nodemailer-gmail-oauth2","4",{"title":6,"description":680},false,"en\u002FNodejs\u002Fnodejs-nodemailer-gmail-oauth2",[691,692,693,694],"Node.js","全端勇士之路 Node.js","OAuth","Nodemailer",null,"2023-07-22 09:56:44","\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F12\u002F28\u002Fnodejs-nodemailer-gmail-oauth2\u002F","erzD_SCAeDK44xvO59zS_H14agcMNqL-pPp6aI0guvg",{"newer":700,"older":704},{"url":701,"title":702,"date":703},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2020\u002F01\u002F07\u002Finstall-nvm-on-windows-10\u002F","Installing and Using nvm on Windows 10 to Switch Node.js Versions","2020-01-07 09:26:33",{"url":705,"title":706,"date":707},"\u002Fen\u002Fhexo\u002F2019\u002F12\u002F25\u002Fswitch-hexo-next-to-algolia-search\u002F","Switching Hexo NexT to Algolia Search","2019-12-25 16:58:13",[709,714,719],{"url":710,"title":711,"date":712,"readingMinutes":713},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2026\u002F01\u002F13\u002Frun-multiple-commands-with-concurrently\u002F","Tired of Opening Multiple Terminals to Run Commands? Use Concurrently","2026-01-13 09:45:28","2",{"url":715,"title":716,"date":717,"readingMinutes":718},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2025\u002F03\u002F13\u002Fhexschool-ecommerce-api-complete-tutorial\u002F","Hexschool Capstone Class Study Group: Complete E-commerce API Tutorial","2025-03-13 09:13:26","9",{"url":720,"title":721,"date":722,"readingMinutes":723},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2024\u002F12\u002F25\u002Fpm2-process-manager-not-pm25\u002F","PM2 Is Process Manager, Not PM2.5","2024-12-25 10:31:33","5",1784011707174]